a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: American jazz keyboardist Adam Holzman (born 15 February 1958, New York City) has played with a wide variety of notable performers and bands – often working as their producer and arranger at the same time.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Adam Holzman

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Grammy Award winner, musical talent and in some regions the most-demanded session guitarist around, Albert Lee is nothing less than world renowned.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Albert Lee

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: As an original member of Bay Area thrashers, Testament, whilst also leading the line for his own namesake jazz trio, Alex Skolnick can do it all.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Alex Skolnick

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Whether he’s writing songs for others, working on production or playing the bass himself André “Dré” Bowman is going to make the bass line something special.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: André "Dré" Bowman

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Andreas Kisser is the lead guitarist for the metalband Sepultura as well as the rock supergroup HAIL! And has worked with acts like Anthrax - this guy’s metal to the bone!
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Andreas Kisser

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Andrew Levy is one of those people in the music industry that seem to have infinite amounts of creativity. Best know (and most comfy) as the bass player for The Brand New Heavies, Andrew is also a proficient songwriter, keyboard player and producer.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Andrew Levy

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: A veritable pioneer of online gear demos, Andy Martin is probably best known as the face, voice and fingers of over 2000 guitar pedal and amp demos for the ProGuitarShop and Reverb.com, earning him the respect and admiration of musicians and gear nerds the world over.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Andy Martin

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: With his virtuoso guitar playing, iconic riffs, and unique take on guitar tone, Andy Summers has solidified his place amongst the biggest guitarists in the history of rock… and rightfully so!
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Andy Summers

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: ANDY WOOD is recognized as part of the forefront of this generation’s top influential guitarists.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Andy Wood

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Holding a B.S. in Music Education with a concentration in jazz guitar from Duquesne University, Arianna Powell is now making her way into Hollywood fame after being named one of the “50 Sensational Female Guitarists” by Guitar Player magazine in 2017.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Arianna Powell

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Guitar virtuoso, singer-songwriter, producer and member of the Canadian JUNO award-winning roots-rock band, Bros. Landreth, Ariel Posen is surely a name to remember in today’s music scene.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Ariel Posen

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Audley Freed has seen his career highlight playing and recording a bestselling live album with Jimmy Page. Over the years he has focused his time and energy as a respected session artist supporting the likes of Joe Perry and The Dixie Chicks.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Audley Freed

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Ben Eller is a popular YouTuber who has gained popularity for his awe-some chops on his guitar lesson series “This is Why You Suck at Guitar”.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Ben Eller

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Meet the man with fearless onstage aerobics and extraordinary musical arrangements, Ben Weinman, He combines intricate speed with depth of feeling on his guitar, garnering admiration from guitarists worldwide.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Ben Weinman

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: From the insane heaviness of March Of The Fireants, the evocative playing of Seabeast, the iconic intro to Blood And Thunder, all the way to the fuzzy goodness of their recent smash hit Curl Of The Burl, Mastodon guitarist Bill Kelliher and his bandmates have set the world of rock and metal ablaze.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Bill Kelliher

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Grammy-nominated producer, engineer, mixer and songwriter Bill Reynolds has built a formidable studio career while maintaining his role as bassist for Band of Horses.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Bill Reynolds

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Billy Morrison is an English guitarist, singer and actor who performs with Billy Idol and the Los Angeles-based cover band Royal Machines.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Billy Morrison

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: With one leg in the brit-rock/indie camp as musical director and co-writer for Morrissey since 1991, and with the other well-rooted in the rockabilly scene through his legendary work with The Polecats, there’s only one word that truly describes Boz Boorer and that is versatility!
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Boz Boorer

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: While attending the Berklee College of Music, Whitford played in various different bands such as Cymbals of Resistance, Earth and Justin Thyme. But Brad Whitford is probably best known as the one of two guitarists for legendary classic rockers Aerosmith.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Brad Whitford

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Brent Hinds is the lead guitarist and singer for technical hybrid metal band Mastodon.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Brent Hinds

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: The hardest working man in the music business, Mr.Nashville Session Musician Himself, Brent Mason is one of the most in-demand guitarists in Country Music. The multiple times Country Guitarist of the Year Award winner has been a game changer for a long time and he’ll remain one for even longer!
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Brent Mason

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Brett Scallions is the lead vocalist and rhythm guitarist for post-grunge rock band Fuel. He has been a responsible for unforgettable hit songs such as 'Hemorrhage', 'Bad Day' and 'Shimmer'.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Brett Scallions

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Brian “Head” Welch is the founder of Love and Death, Co-founder of KORN and a true metal head by heart. He has inspired many with his marvelous skills on the guitar.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Brian "Head" Welch

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: ‘The Show Most Go On’, ‘We will Rock You’ and ‘I Want It All’ are classic hits that we have all sung our hearts out to at some point, and all of them have the signature of world-renowned guitarist Brian May.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Brian May

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Brian Nutter is a tone monster and massive guitar player. Equally proficient in a number of styles, Brian masters rock, country, metal and some exciting styles in-between!
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Brian Nutter

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Bryan is a member of Supergroup The Aristocrats with Guthrie Govan and Marco Minnemann. He also plays in what might be called The Monkees of death metal, Dethklok from the animated Adult Swim show Metalocalypse.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Bryan Beller

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Ron 'Bumblefoot' Thal is an award-winning vocalist, songwriter, producer and world-renowned guitar virtuoso, with over 20 years of releasing music, playing international festivals and headlining tours, and gracing magazine covers as a solo artist.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Bumblefoot

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Carles Benavent, aka La Garza Flamenca, was born and raised in the Barcelonan neighbourhood Poble Sec in the 1950s. At an age of thirteen, when Carles first started playing the bass, he was attracted to the bluesy and rocky tunes of the time - Jimi Hendrix in particular.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Carles Benavent

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Carlitos Del Puerto is already one of the most recognized acoustic bass players to emerge in the last decade. Even at the young age of 30, it’s no surprise that Carlitos Is able to play with such virtuosity and maturity, as he is the son of world famous Cuban bass player, Carlos Del Puerto.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Carlos Del Puerto

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Charles Cave is the youthful bassist, backing vocalist and the primary songwriter in the Indie rockers White Lies. The band, which started off as ‘Fear of Flying’, transformed into the White Lies persona in 2007 to better match their evolving style of music.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Charles Cave

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: From teenage heartthrob to blues-rock star to six-string slinger for the biggest names in rock history. Charlie Sexton has tried it all, and must be considered a full-blown guitar legend in his own right!
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Charlie Sexton

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Chip Shearin is a highly recognized bass player, composer and an astonishing record producer. On top of performing and producing, he runs KEO Music Recordings, an indie label distributed by Warner Bros.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Chip Shearin

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Chris Minh Doky is arguably one of the most proficient bass players in Jazz today. Equally adept at double- and electric bass, Chris has known runaway success as both a soloist and as a sideman, where he worked with everyone from Mike Stern to David Sanborn.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Chris Minh Doky

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: This multitalented string virtuoso is one to pay attention to in the near future! Not only is Cody Wright the bass player in Jonathan Scales Fourchestra he’s also the guitarist in his own trio. Cody is becoming a world-class musician of the highest order.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Cody Wright

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Colin Scott, the man behind CSGuitars, picked up the guitar relatively late but has made up for lost time through his work as blogger, guitar player, luthier, and festival arranger.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Colin Scott

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Dammo Farmer, a native of Chicago, Illinois, has established himself as an incredible talent amongst musicians in the industry today.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Dammo Farmer

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Daniel Donato is nothing short of a guitar prodigy, and at the tender age of 20 he is currently seen as one of the hottest names in the Nashville Country scene where he’s currently playing with the Don Kelley Band.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Daniel Donato

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Dan Huff began his career in the melodic rock band Giant. Since then, he has found work as a session guitarist and producer, in both rock and country music, and the long list of artist he has played with includes Michael Jackson, Michael Bolton, Mariah Carey and Celine Dion.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Dann Huff

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: For more than 30 years Darryl Jones has played with some of the greatest legends of the jazz and rock world. For many he is best known for his gig with The Rolling Stones ranging from 1994 and onwards.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Darryl Jones

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Dave Catching stands as a true godfather of stoner and desert rock. The list of artists he has worked with through the years is endless, but he is most famous for wielding the guitar with bands such as Queens of the Stoneage and Eagles of Death Metal
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Dave Catching

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: LaRue’s technical prowess is formidable among other jazz-fusionists, but his unique talent is to project his virtuosity with remarkable soul and feel.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Dave LaRue

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Dave Stewart, the world-famous British-born legendary musician, producer, author, filmmaker, philanthropist and innovator really needs no introduction. He is regarded as an iconic figure in the world of music and beyond.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Dave Stewart

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: For the last 13 years, the only constant in Steve Vai’s touring career has been guitarist Dave Weiner.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Dave Weiner

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: David Wallimann was born in Aix-en Provence, South France in 1977. He started playing the guitar at the age of 15, and pursued an education in studying advanced guitar at the CMA School of Music in Valenciennes, where he graduated with honors.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: David Wallimann

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: For close to 30 years guitarist/composer/arranger/educator Dean Brown has been an integral part of the global fusion and contemporary jazz scene. Those who have seen and heard Dean Brown perform are immediately struck by the passion and energy he puts into each note.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Dean Brown

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Debra Killings is an American singer and bass guitarist, notable for an extensive session and background vocal work for LaFace Records and Rowdy Records-based artists such as TLC, Monica and OutKast.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Debra Killings

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: American keyboardist Derek Sherinian has amazed all with his cool attitude topped off with an impressive and diverse resume. He has played and toured for A-list musicians including Alice Cooper, Billy Idol, Kiss and Black Label Society.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Derek Sherinian

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: The extraordinary bassist and composer Derrick Hodge has an amazing jazz groove and is the winner of the award Rising star – Electric bass by Downbeat. He has worked with some of Philly’s finest and has evolved into a versatile soloist with the impressive debut album “Live Today”.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Derrick Hodge

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Derrick Lee Murdock (aka Dock) was born in Philadelphia and began playing the bass at 17.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Derrick Lee Murdock

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Canadian musician, songwriter and record producer Devin Townsend amazes all with his creativity. He spits out deep and versatile albums en masse and always delivers top quality music.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Devin Townsend

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Divinity Roxx is the bass player and Musical Director in Beyoncé’s band Suga Mama, an all female group created specifically to accompany Beyoncé. As a solo musician, Roxx is currently working on The Roxx Boxx Experience, her second album due to come out this year.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Divinity Roxx

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Don Airey is one of the most productive men on keyboard. With more than 280 albums and recordings with the industry’s finest he boosts quantity with quality all the way.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Don Airey

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Doug Aldrich is one of the world's true rock stars. Equally adept at playing soaring, heartfelt leads and rocking rhythms, Doug's versatility and tasty tones make him a force to be reckoned with.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Doug Aldrich

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: One of rock’s true success stories, Duff McKagan’s resume includes larger-than-life bands Guns’n’Roses and Velvet Revolver. He’s an accomplished musician playing virtually anything from drums to bass to guitar, a columnist, a writer and a businessman. Plus he fronts his own band, Loaded.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Duff McKagan

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Dweezil Zappa is the son of Frank Zappa, so it was inevitable that from the moment of his birth, his life would be filled wall-to wall with music (his father having listed his religion as “musician” on Dweezil’s birth certificate).
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Dweezil Zappa

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Emily Kokal is one of the co-founders of the indie rock band, Warpaint, known for its art rocky, dream pop and psychedelic rock style with enough time changes to satisfy even the most bearded prog-fanatics.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Emily Kokal

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Eric originally started out as a drummer (we all have our mistakes) but quickly switched to bass at the age 15. Eric says that being a drummer first has really helped him focus on solid grooves and has enabled him to develop a rock solid sense of timing.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Eric Smith

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Ethan Farmer AKA EBassMan is one of the most confident bass players you’re ever likely to meet. His talent and musicality speak for themselves, but it’s his charisma and personality that makes this cat so special. While he cut his teeth on gospel, this guy oozes funk from every single pore!
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Ethan "EBassman" Farmer

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Federico Malaman is revitalizing jazz fusion for the modern audience, while exuding an exuberant joy of playing. If you want to be mesmerized by remarkable chops, look no further.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Federico Malaman

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: His surname may mean beautiful in spanish, but when coupled with the common first name Frank, Bello means "certain doom". His name is synonymous with the heaviest of metal and an anagram for "mean shredder" (don´t check, just trust me on this). Frank Bello undoubtedly is a living bass legend.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Frank Bello

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Gail Ann Dorsey is a top session bassist and vocalist with an eclectic and impressive career. She has been associated with being the bassist for David Bowie since 1995 to present day and not least as being a solo recording artist during her incredible career spanning two decades.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Gail Ann Dorsey

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Gary Holt is the talented lead guitarist and songwriter in the American thrash metal band Exodus.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Gary Holt

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: A world class guitar hero, a Grammy-nominated songwriter and composer, an international recording artist with over 20 acclaimed solo albums to date, and a soundtrack composer for film and television, Gary Lucas is on the move in 2013.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Gary Lucas

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Gary Willis is an American bassist and composer, primarily known as the co-founder of the jazz fusion band Tribal Tech. Aside from his work in Tribal Tech, Willis has risen to fame working with numerous other jazz musicians including Wayne Shorter, Dennis Chambers and Allan Holdsworth.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Gary Willis

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Originally from Minnesota, Eric Whorton aka. Gearmanndude was raised on 70's Country Music and AM Radio soft rock, but was eventually drawn to the six string by Eddie Van Halen, and the allure of 80's hair bands.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Gearmanndude

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Operating out of Ontario, Canada, Glenn Fricker is the face of Spectre Sound Studios YouTube channel. He is an experienced recording engineer with more than 20 years of experience recording hard rock and metal acts professionally.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Glenn Fricker

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Jean-Christophe Maillard, a.k.a. Le Grand Baton is a composer, guitarist, pianist, singer/songwriter and arranger.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Grand Baton

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Wisconsin guitarist Greg Koch is a master guitarist, who skillfully works through blues, jazz, country, funk. Koch has his hands on music clinics, instructional videos, and plays with various lineups. On top of that, he’s a comedian in disguise.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Greg Koch

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Just saying his name out loud three times in front of a guitar unleashes awesome licks. He's completely mastered rock, blues, jazz and shred and combines them into a sound that is thoroughly exciting.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Guthrie Govan

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Born into a family of musicians, Hadrien Feraud began studying guitar at age 8, taking lessons from his father. Young Hadrien was actually more interested in playing drums until he received a copy of Jaco Pastorius’ The Birthday Concert CD at age 12.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Hadrien Feraud

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Harry McVeigh lends his unspeakably precise vocals and invigorating guitar skills to British alternative rock band sensation, White Lies.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Harry McVeigh

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Knowledgeable, honest, and energetic, Henning Pauly aka. EytschPi42, is not just a guitar player, but a skilled producer, composer, and entrepreneur.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Henning Pauly

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Henrik Linder combines beauty with dirty sounds and amazing chops with great creative vision.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Henrik Linder

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Hua Dong gave up his major in German language to pursue his dream of being a professional musician. It turned out to be a very good decision.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Hua Dong

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Being the former bass player for none other than the late, great Prince should say something about Ida's musicianship and deep knowledge of the funk. These days, she is touring with her solo project, spreading the funk far and wide.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Ida Nielsen

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: INORAN is a Japanese guitarist known from the band Luna Sea, a legendary rock band that was founded in 1989, originally calling themselves Lunacy.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Inoran

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Ishibashi Gakki was founded in 1938 and is one of the most recognized musical instrument retailers in Japan with 15 stores selling guitars, amplifiers, effect pedals, drums, keyboards, recording gear and other music oriented equipment as well as books and musical scores.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Ishibashi

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Jón "Jónsi" Þór Birgisson is an exceptional musician, whose signature move is playing guitar with a cello bow. Often praised as an otherworldly angel, Jónsi in fact does strike a lot like one because of his angelic falsetto voice.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Jónsi

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: The best guitarist in Nashville? JD Simo blends the best elements of blazing, tasteful, authoritative country guitar with a great mix of the best of Cream-era Eric Clapton and a touch of Peter Green of Fleetwood Mac – with that recipe we are in for a full course meal in guitar heaven.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: J.D. Simo

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Jack Gibson is the long tenured bass player for celebrated US thrash metal group Exodus. He’s been rocking with the band since 1996 and shows no signs of slowing down.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Jack Gibson

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Jacob Binzer is the lead guitarist of the Danish hard rock group D-A-D. For nearly 30 years his country-inspired heavy riffs and sublime soloes have been a key element in the group’s Cow-punk style.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Jacob "Cobber" Binzer

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: From blues-rock to jazz while crossing over into the world of classical compositions, London-based guitarist, Jake Willson is currently one the most exciting new voices in the world of guitar-oriented music.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Jake Willson

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Commanding bass, shredding twin guitars, hard drumming and aggressive vocals equals hit metal band, Korn. James “Munky” Shaffer is one hard-hitting guitarist that plays the strings in powerful Korn and we are very excited that Shaffer uses our TC gear to spike his sound on- and off stage.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: James 'Munky' Shaffer

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: London born US based artist, bass player, record producer, author and educator Janek Gwizdala has been on the international music scene for over 15 years. He dropped out early from both The Royal Academy of Music in London and Berklee College of Music in Boston to pursue his own musical journey.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Janek Gwizdala

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Jason Hook is the lead guitarist of US metal band Five Finger Death Punch.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Jason Hook

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: From ferocious high-speed shredding to tender melancholic melodies, Jen Majura of modern-metal giants Evanescence covers it all, making her guitar playing as fierce, fearless and ambitious as herself.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Jen Majura

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Jennifer Lindberg is one of the co-founders of the indie rock band, War-paint, known for its art rocky, dream pop and psychedelic rock style with enough time changes to satisfy even the most bearded prog-fanatics.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Jennifer Lindberg

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Great licks, great sounds and a musicloving, genuinly nice guy - That's Jerry McPherson.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Jerry McPherson

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Jimmy Chiang is undoubtly the top session guitar player in China. He has done countless guitar tracks and has a great influence on Chinese pop music.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Jimmy Chiang

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Based in Brighton, England, a city with a vibrant math-rock scene, Joe Branton was always into progressive, boundary seeking music.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Joe Branton

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Joe Perry’s name is synonymous with the raw six-string energy that gives rock phenomenon Aerosmith their trademark edge. The power and craftsmanship of his guitar playing has transfixed fans for over 30 years and placed him in rock’n’roll history.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Joe Perry

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Knowing when to go full throttle and when to hold back a bit on your instrument is essential to any musician. As the highly regarded bass player for Danish art rock band Mew, Johan Wohlert has perfected the classic rock n roll craft of timing and modesty.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Johan Wohlert

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: John 5 is a guitarist that defies regular norms by mastering styles ranging from bluegrass to shred metal. Besides playing for Rob Zombie, he’s collaborated with David Lee Roth and Marilyn Manson and has released several well-received instrumental albums.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: John 5

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: John S. Konesky is a Grammy Award winning American guitarist, additional vocalist, producer and actor. He has been called a mythical guitar god and whether it is in Tenacious D, Trainwreck, The Kyle Gass Band or his solo work, his excellent guitar playing definitely lives up to the nickname.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: John Konesky

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: John Petrucci is one of the most technically gifted guitar players in the world and, as one of the founders of Dream Theater, has enjoyed enormous critical and commercial success selling around 8 million albums worldwide.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: John Petrucci

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: With his unique blend of styles ranging from rock, jazz and blues mixed with a copious use of the guitars whammy bar, Johnny A has really managed to set himself apart from the rest of the guitar-wielding pack.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Johnny A

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Johnny Hiland was practically born with a guitar in his hand and with bluegrass music in his blood. At the tender age of ten, he won a talent show that put him in front of an audience in New York City. At that time he’d already been touring with the family band for several years.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Johnny Hiland

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Jon Thorne has grown a highly respected reputation for his innovative approach and style on the double bass. He took an instrument that is typically rooted in a more contemporary and classical genre of music and interpreted it into Lamb’s experimental electronic sound with great success.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Jon Thorne

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Jona Weinhofen is responsible for the hard-edged guitar eclecticism coming from Australian based I Killed the Prom Queen. He’s also rocked bands like Brit metalcore act Bring Me the Horizon and Californian group Bleeding Through.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Jona Weinhofen

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Jonathan Hischke is a bass player who’s not afraid to dive head first into sounds that seem peculiar, if not downright obscene. He’s here to challenge the traditional way a bass player approaches his instrument. He’s here to make some noise!
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Jonathan Hischke

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Jordan Rudess’ virtuoso keyboard skills that combine blazing fast runs with an amazing ear for catchy melodies and all-encompassing soundscapes have seen him transcend the typical keyboard player’s ensemble role, and moved him to the front as one of our times best musicians.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Jordan Rudess

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Josh Smith is what you might call a blues prodigy. He has been playing since he was 3, and gigging steadily since 13 or 14.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Josh Smith

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Juan Alderete is an American bassist known for his work with the bands Racer X and The Mars Volta. He is famous for his copious use of effects, and his wide-ranging playing techniques. These skills have allowed him to play a variety of musical styles, from jazz, to heavy metal and progressive rock.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Juan Alderete

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Justin Meldal-Johnsen's highly sought after skills and musical interpretation has equated to an illustrious career that has seen him contribute to the arts as a bass performer, producer, songwriter and musical director for artists as diverse as Beck, Nine Inch Nails and Tori Amos.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Justin Meldal-Johnsen

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: K5 is primarily known as the guitar player in NAMBA69 with the legendary punk bass player Akihiro Namba.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: K5

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Keith Gattis is country through-and-through: down-to-earth focused, hard working and with some killer tone!
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Keith Gattis

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: KenKen is an incredible bass player, belonging to one of Japan's most iconic 3 piece rock bands RIZE.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: KenKen

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Kern has performed with an abundance of amazing artists such as Lady Gaga, Beyonce, Mary J. Blige, Jeezy, Ne-Yo, Brandy, Ciara, Chris Brown, Destiny's Child, Faith Evans, R. Kelly, Salt N Pepa, Boys II Men, Black Street, Aaliyah, New Kids On The Block and Bobby Brown.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Kern Brantley

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Kirk Fletcher is what you might call “The Real Deal”. A younger blues guitarist that can hang with the greatest blues guitarists in history. In fact he has played with several legendary blues guitarists and is fast on his way to becoming one himself.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Kirk Fletcher

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Knox Chandler is a New York based guitarist and cellist. He is known as a session musician but his musical career has spun widely including touring recording, arranging and producing several known for three decades.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Knox Chandler

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Lari Basilio was born into a musical household in São Paulo, Brazil, with her father being an accomplished singer and acoustic guitar player.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Lari Basilio

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Larry Mitchell is a Grammy award-winning producer, engineer and performer who has toured the world playing guitar with well-known artists including Tracy Chapman, Billy Squier, Ric Ocasek and Miguel Bosé. He also fronts the dynamic rock/instrumental band The Larry Mitchell Trio.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Larry Mitchell

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Leda is a Japanese guitarist / songwriter who is primarily known from the bands DELUHI and UNDIVIDE.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Leda

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Lee Ranaldo, born in 1956, is one of the original members of the American avant-garde band Sonic Youth.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Lee Ranaldo

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Growing up in L.A. in the 60′s, Grammy award winning guitarist Lee Ritenour received a rich cross section of exposure to jazz, rock and Brazilian music.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Lee Ritenour

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Known for the popular Frog Leap Studios YouTube channel, Leo Moracchioli is a rock musician and producer from Norway.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Leo Moracchioli

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: As one of Denmark’s most popular touring guitarists and the live guitarist for acclaimed art rockers Mew, Mads Wegner have worked his thick guitar sound into the ears of concert-goers for two decades.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Mads Wegner

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Mark Holcomb is lead guitarist in the modern progressive metal band Periphery and his heavy killer-riffs can also be experienced in the extreme metal duo Haunted Shores, a studio project with fellow Periphery lead guitarist Misha Mansoor.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Mark Holcomb

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: There is no doubt that throughout his impressive career Mark King has been one of the most significant contributors in developing the voice of modern electric bass playing.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Mark King

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Mark Lettieri is a guitarist, composer and producer from Fort Worth, TX known for his groovy yet highly emotive guitar playing with fusion super-group Snarky Puppy as well as under his own name.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Mark Lettieri

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: If you play bass and you have an Internet connection, chances are you’ve seen MarloweDK (Thomas Risell)’s channel. This Copenhagen, Denmark native started his YouTube channel in 2006 and has been serving a wide variety of super useful bass lessons on his channel, which has had over 25 million views.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: MarloweDK

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Hailing from Leipzig, Germany, Martin Miller is making a name for himself as a professional musician and an inspiring and knowledgeable guitar teacher.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Martin Miller

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: As a solo artist, Spender is not your run of the mill singer-songwriter-strumming-cowboy-chords performer. With her rich voice, passionate singing and jaw-dropping fingerstyle playing, Spender is something else entirely.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Mary Spender

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Brazilian guitar prodigy and social media shooting star, Mateus Asato, is making his presence felt with his tasteful, melodic playing and annoyingly good technique, mastering everything from bluesy soul and jazzy ballads to shredding metal.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Mateus Asato

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Matt Beck is a true multi instrumentalist, playing guitar, keyboards, mandolin, banjo, lap-Steel, dobro, bass and cavaquinho as well as singing.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Matt Beck

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Melvin is one of the most highly-demanded session bass players worldwide touring and performing with the Pointer Sisters, Chaka Khan, David Benoit, Russ Freeman Project, Bryan Ferry, George Duke, and Lee Ritenour, just to name a few industry greats.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Melvin Lee Davis

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Michael ’Padge’ Paget, born 1978, is the lead guitarist in Welsh heavy metal band Bullet for My Valentine. The band is famous for their catchy vocals, aggressive riffs and haunting melodies. Padge gets his inspiration from heavy players like James Hetfield and Dimebag Darrell
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Michael 'Padge' Paget

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Michael Britt is probably best known as the twanging guitar player of the American country music group Lonestar.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Michael Britt

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Michael Shuman, affectionately named ‘Mikey Shoes’ by some, has come to be known for his stage antics and tremendous bass skills for the heavy rock outfit ‘Queens of the Stone Age’.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Michael Shuman

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Mika Vandborg is known as one of the most talented and respected guitarists in Denmark. He has appeared on numerous recordings and has toured with some of the best musicians and artists such as Justin Hawkins, Love Shop, Gnags, Ida Corr, Mads Langer, Dicte and Claus Hempler to name a few.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Mika Vandborg

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Mike Dawes is an English guitar player known for composing, arranging and performing multiple parts simultaneously on one instrument using unique extended and micro-techniques. He is hailed as one of the world’s finest and most creative modern fingerstyle guitar performers.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Mike Dawes

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: American jazz guitarist Mike Stern was voted the Best Jazz Guitarist of 1993 by Guitar Player magazine. Through his career he has play with some of the worlds most prominent jazz musicians and released a dozen solo albums. At age 60 Stern doesn’t seem to be slowing down.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Mike Stern

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Named as one of the next generation’s big six-string legends by Rolling Stone Magazine, Misha Mansoor is currently paving the way for the new era of progressive metal with his gut-punching riffs and keen ear for catchy melodies.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Misha Mansoor

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Hailed as a “phenomenon” by legendary guitar virtuoso, Steve Vai, who was blown away by her soulful chops and extraordinary connection with her instrument, 22-year-old Mohini Dey has already established herself as one of the most talented bass players of her generation.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Mohini Dey

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Self-taught on the bass, MonoNeon’s killer groove and endless string of over-the-barline fills have left both audiences and fellow bass players jaw-to-the-floor.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: MonoNeon

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Nathan East is the Swiss Army knife of bassists. His extraordinary talent and versatility has led him to playing and recording across genres with the biggest talents in the music industry such as Michael Jackson, George Harrison, Barry White, Madonna, Whitney Houston, Phil Collins, and many more
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Nathan East

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Nick Beggs is currently the bass player for Steven Wilson and Kim Wilde. Over the years he has played with a huge number of artists including his own band Kajagoogoo, Steve Hackett and John Paul Jones.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Nick Beggs

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Ever since Reinhart tried his first guitar pedal, he was intrigued by what effects could for musical composition. As such, guitar effects have become an integral part of Reinhart’s playing and his mastery over the sounds you can coax from different constellations of effects is second to none.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Nick Reinhart

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: With a unique funky playing style, an angelic singing voice and an extremely powerful stage presence, Nik West is currently one of the hottest names on the bass scene.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Nik West

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Omar Rodríguez-López is art incarnate - he’s a multi-instrumentalist who is active in music, film and writing. Perhaps best known through The Mars Volta, At the Drive-in and as a solo artist.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Omar Rodríguez-López

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Orianthi is an Australian guitarist, perhaps best known as the guitarist of the late Michael Jackson, but her solo career is taking off big time as well. She picked up the guitar when she was eleven and has played with the likes of Steve Vai and Carlos Santana.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Orianthi

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Born in Israel, Oz started his professional career at the age of 13 playing jazz, blues, pop and rock music.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Oz Noy

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Pat Buchanan is one of Nashville's top session guitarists and has been so for many years now. Pat Buchanan has played the axe in many parts of the US and abroad all his life.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Pat Buchanan

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Paul Brandon Gilbert is known for his technical guitar work with Racer X and Mr. Big. He has been voted number 4 on a list in GuitarOne magazine of the "Top 10 Greatest Guitar Shredders of All Time", and holds a spot in Guitar Worlds 50 Fastest Guitarists of All Time list.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Paul Gilbert

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Paul Riario rocketed to fame as the tech editor of Guitar World. The classic 'hey this is Paul from Guitar World and today we'll be looking at ..." has a guaranteed place in the brain of every guitarist under 40.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Paul Riario

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Paulo Jr. is the longest remaining member of metal band Sepultura rocking the bass since ’85. Besides playing bass he is a soccer lover and a charity man as well.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Paulo Xisto Pinto Jr.

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Peredur ap Gwynedd is a Welsh guitarist, born and raised in South Wales. Ap Gwynedd is mostly known as a member of the Australian rock/electronica band, Pendullum, but he has also performed with acts such as Natalie Imbruglia, Norman Cook, Sophie Ellis Bextor and Mylene Farmer.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Peredur Ap Gwynedd

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: As a studio guitarist for producer Linda Perry, Peter Thorn has played on albums by Courtney Love, Alicia Keys, Daniel Powter, Ben Jelen, and others.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Pete Thorn

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Phil Campbell is the guitarist of rock behemoths Motörhead, and responsible for delivering some of the dirtiest, sexiest most fist-pumping riffs and licks in the history of rock.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Phil Campbell

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Phil Demmel was all set to quit the music business, when he agreed to go on one last tour with friend and former band-mate Robb Flynn’s band Machine Head. The chemistry turned out to be undeniable, and the rest, as they say, is history.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Phil Demmel

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Born in 1966, Philip Xenidis started playing the guitar at the age of five, when his father brought home an electric guitar for him. Barely able to hold the guitar, he kept at it, and today we know him simply as Phil X!
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Phil X

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Three-time Grammy nominee and Emmy Award-winning bassist Philip Bynoe is a prolific recording and touring musician. Though best known for his work with virtuoso guitarist Steve Vai, Philip has played everything from heavy metal to R&B to classical.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Philip Bynoe

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Phillip McKnight is a luthier who started building and repairing basses and guitars in 2003. He is known throughout the industry for having a seemingly endless knowledge of instruments, and gear, as well the ins and outs of the music business.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Phillip McKnight

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Steve aka. PixxyLixx like his popular YouTube channel is a guitar vlogger out of Boston, Massachussets. With his formative years solidly placed in the 80’s, Pixxy’s playing style is heavily influenced by the top shredders of the hair metal era.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: PixxyLixxx

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Reeves Gabrels is an American guitarist/songwriter/producer. He is best known (since 2012) as a member of The Cure, an English band with an international audience, as well as for his close collaboration with David Bowie from 1987 to 2000.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Reeves Gabrels

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Riginald “Fieldy” Arvizu plays a mean bass in KoRn. His percussive style on the bass inspired by hiphop music fronts the metal phenomenon with one-of-a-kind bass lines. In total a crazy dude that rocks hard.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Reginald "Fieldy" Arvizu

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Versatile rock guitar player Richard Fortus of Guns N’ Roses, currently touring with Thin Lizzy (2011) and Guns n' Roses, is a sought after dedicated guitar player. Prior to joining Guns N’ Roses in 2002, Richard played with his band Pale Divine and toured as supporting act for Psychedelic Furs.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Richard Fortus

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: For people who like fusion with prominent guitar playing, the name Richard Hallebeek should sound familiar. His unique style and lyrical phrasing have solidified his position as one of the best within his genre, and have seen him collaborate with several jazz/fusion legends throughout his career.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Richard Hallebeek

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: The American guitarist and producer Rob Caggiano, born on the 7th of November 1976, is probably best known as the lead guitarist of the thrash pioneers Anthrax.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Rob Caggiano

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Rob Chapman is a professional guitarist from Wiltshire in the United Kingdom. He’s become internationally renowned due to his hilarious guitar based review and tuition videos on his YouTube channel.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Rob Chapman

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: 5 times Grammy nominee Robben Ford is the premier electric guitarist of today. He is known for his excellent blues playing and ability to be comfortable in a variety of musical contexts. A magnificent blend of jazz and blues truly defines him as a guitarist.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Robben Ford

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: As an original member of the Doors, Robby Krieger’s playing and songwriting has permeated modern pop-culture as the soundtrack of an entire era.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Robby Krieger

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Robert Levon Been is one of the founding members of Black Rebel Motorcycle Club. He is best known as a bassist and singer, and his crushing tone and distinct voice acts as the cornerstone of BRMC's unique sound.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Robert Levon Been

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: ‘Burn’, ‘Highway Star’ and ‘Smoke on the Water’ are chart-toppers by world-renowned Deep Purple and Roger Glover is laying down the bass lines in this influential rock band. Roger is one of the true bass pioneers of rock and we are extremely proud that he is using our gear to spike his sound.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Roger Glover

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Bass player and producer Roscoe Beck maintains the pulse, with a mainline to the blues.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Roscoe Beck

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Rudy Sarzo is nothing less than a legend on the bass guitar. His more than 35 years in music includes membership of awesome bands like Ozzy Osbourne, Quiet Riot, White Snake, DIO, Blue Öyster Cult and many others. He has played on a number of records that have sold in excess of 30 million copies.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Rudy Sarzo

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Ryan Monroe is a well-rounded multi-instrumentalist, best known for his role as a keyboard and guitar player in Band of Horses.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Ryan Monroe

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Guitarist and singer-songwriter Ryan Roxie, born in California, currently resides in Stockholm, Sweden. He is the founding member of Roxie 77 and probably best known for his guitar work with Slash’s Snakepit and legendary harbinger of rock and roll, Alice Cooper.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Ryan Roxie

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: The ferocious days of the 80’s hairspray kings on Sunset Strip may be long gone, but audiences worldwide still crave good lookin’ dudes with pouty lips, eyeliner and voluminous hair the length of a model’s legs playing glamorous sounding rock anthems.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Satchel

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Known for his superb online lessons – and a black silk glove – Scott Devine uses his masterful chops to guide bassists of all levels to achieve their musical goals and become better musicians.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Scott Devine

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Scott Holiday is the riff happy lead guitarist of the American blues rock band Rival Sons. He is also a former member of the bands Human Lab and Black Summer Crush. And, a self-proclaimed guitar dork.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Scott Holiday

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Scott Ian has helped pioneer the soaring sound of thrash metal band Anthrax with his crunchy guitar riffs. Over the last 30 years, he’s worked on creating the “New Wave of American Heavy Metal” and has been a constant figure in the world of music, comics, poker, movies and television.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Scott Ian

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Sean Michael Ray is the type of bass player that can produce pure, melodic, soul-stirring sounds that truly captures an audience.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Sean Michael Ray

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: From the sunny coast of Southern California, Sean Piece Johnson brings his passion for music and the guitar to the world through his band, Cockeyed Optimist, and his growing YouTube channel.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Sean Pierce Johnson

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Soren Andersen is a Danish guitarist, producer and songwriter, located in Copenhagen, Denmark. He works as a touring guitarist for Glenn Hughes and Mike Tramp. He does most of his productions in the Medley Studios, which he co-owns. He has worked with artists such as Artillery, Jay Nash and Baal
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Soren Andersen

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: From Alice Cooper to Sheila E and Huey Lewis to Vasco Rossi there is one constant in Stef Burns’ effects rack: TC Electronic!
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Stef Burns

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Steffen Schackinger is a Danish studio guitarist, composer and performing artist. Inspired by Mark Knopfler and Jimi Hendrix, Steffen quickly made his mark on the Danish music scene, playing with different bands both in Denmark and abroad.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Steffen Schackinger

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Stephen Carpenter lead guitarist in Deftones, underscores the groups melodic vocals with a heavily distorted guitar sound that is purely distilled metal.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Stephen "Stef" Carpenter

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Steve Lawson is a man of many talents including playing the bass guitar excellent and looping just the same. Also, he is full of passion for music, not just his own, but all music and musicians.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Steve Lawson

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Steve Morse is best known as the founder of the Dixie Dregs, and guitar player in Deep Purple since 1994. Morse's career has encompassed genres rock, country, funk, jazz, classical, and fusion.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Steve Morse

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Steve Stevens is one of the most gifted guitarists to emerge from the ’80s music scene. Stevens picked up the acoustic guitar at only seven years of age and by the age of 13 he got his first electric guitar and was soon influenced by early progressive rock bands like Genesis, Yes and King Crimson.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Steve Stevens

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: In guitar, the order of technical prowess is: amateur – pro – virtuoso – guitar genius – Steve Vai. When it comes to technical skills, few have been able to come close him for the last 20 years.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Steve Vai

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Ever prolific English musician Steven Wilson has been hard at work at various musical projects, amongst others Porcupine Tree, over the last couple of decades, playing guitar as well as several other instruments while trying out different musical genres.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Steven Wilson

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Sune Rose Wagner is the songwriter, guitarist, and vocalist for noise pop duo, The Raveonettes. He has been a member of three successful bands, had twice as many albums figuring on the US Billboard Top 200 and scored a 2 million $ recording contract with a major label before turning 40.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Sune Rose Wagner

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Syu, lead guitarists in one of the best Japanese heavy metal bands, Galneryus’s, was initially playing violin until he, at the age of ten, switched to electric guitar, to play more heavy rock music.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Syu

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Tal Wilkenfeld is a musical marvel; the kind of dynamic young talent whose fresh vision and uncanny intuition puts a whole new perspective on an age-old art form.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Tal Wilkenfeld

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: That's us. You know about us, right? We're the guys completely dedicated to making the best guitar-and bass effects out there, period. We are all very passionate about music and most of us are active musicians and nuts about guitar and bass effects - so we know a thing or two about tone.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: TC Electronic

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Since its inception in 2015, it’s safe to say that That Pedal Show has also become THE pedal show to watch on YouTube. With a massive dedicated following and over 15 million views, rest assured that every Friday, Dan and Mick are releasing another viral video.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: That Pedal Show

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Long before YouTube and his coronation as The Tone King, Louis got his first guitar as a 6th grader, a white flying V that reminded him of KK Downing’s axe.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: The Tone King

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Thomas Blugs Strat® sound touches your heart like no other. In 1997 he was awarded "best German rock+pop guitarist" and in 2004 he became “Strat King” of Europe for Fender.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Thomas Blug

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Tim Lefebvre possesses the willingness and ability to speak the language of those around him, which has led him to be on speed dial for countless artists. He produces, composes, remixes and of course plays a killer bass.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Tim Lefebvre

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: One of the nicest guys in show business, Tom Hamilton, holds down the low end in the hard rock/blues rock band Aerosmith and has even co-written 2 of their greatest hits: "Sweet Emotion" and "Janie's Got a Gun".
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Tom Hamilton

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: British fusion jazz virtuoso, Tom Quayle, is a master of fluid legato improvisation and an accomplished guitar instructor, hosting masterclasses all over the world.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Tom Quayle

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: TonePrint Junkies is a self-help group for addicts of all things TonePrint! A Facebook group started and managed by TC Electronic customers, users and fanatics, TonePrint Junkies has over 3000 members and is growing daily. Come join us and help spread the disease!
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: TonePrint Junkies

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Multi-instrumentalist, composer and bass player Tony Grey is known for his 6 string electric bass technique and for jazz world fusion compositions.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Tony Grey

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Tres Gilbert is one of Atlanta's top bass players and one of the hardest working guys in the industry.Tres is also a highly regarded record producer and a member of the TC Bass Street Team.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Tres Gilbert

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: California-based guitar blogger, Trey Xavier, is the man behind the Gear Gods channel on YouTube, delivering metal-centric content to a horde of virtual metal heads.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Trey Xavier

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Troy McLawhorn has left his mark on the alternative rock and metal scene of the early noughties, contributing his axe-wielding skills to acts such as doubleDrive, Sevendust, Dark New Day, Seether and Evanescence.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Troy McLawhorn

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Troy Sanders rocks the bass lines and vocals in the hugely successful American heavy metal band, Mastodon, which is famous for their hard-rocking riffs, psychedelic multi-layered songs and great melodies.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Troy Sanders

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Troy Dean Van Leeuwen began playing music at a young age and started playing guitar at age 13. He soon became a sought after session player, which later led him to join such legendary rock bands as A Perfect Circle and Queens of the Stone Age.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Troy Van Leeuwen

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: After stumbling across the guitar sorceries of Eric Johnson’s Cliffs of Dover and Van Halen’s Eruption at his uncle’s house, Tyler Larson, like so many other young men, was hooked for life.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Tyler Larson

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Danish guitar-virtuoso and local hero, Uffe Steen, is slowly but surely making his presence felt on the internet with his absolutely breathtaking chops and imaginative playing.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Uffe Steen

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Uriah Duffy is an American bassist best known for his five-year stint with 80’s hard rock band Whitesnake. In addition to Whitesnake, Duffy has shown his talent across genres and recorded with a number of high profile artists, including Christina Aguilera and Alicia Keys.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Uriah Duffy

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Uwe Hassbecker, born 1960 in East Germany, is a German guitarist primarily known for his work with the band Silly.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Uwe Hassbecker

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: What would the world of music be like without the eclectic guitar playing of Living Colour’s Vernon Reid? A less inspiring and honest place for sure. This legend has already left a massive mark on music history and continue to do so today!
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Vernon Reid

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Victor Wooten redefines the word musician. Five time Grammy Award winner, three times Bass Player of the Year winner and acclaimed as one of the Top Ten Bassists of All Time by Rolling Stone Magazine, Victor Wooten is an idol to many musicians.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Victor Wooten

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Walter Barnes Jr. is a musician extraordinaire. He can be found producing, writing, singing, and performing on his bass with numerous celebrities and recording artists.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Walter Barnes Jr.

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Wes Geer rose to fame as the guitar player in the cross-over metal band Hed P.E. Since then things haven't exactly slowed down for Wes lately, as he was chosen by metal giants Korn as their touring guitar player, replacing Brian ”Head” Welch on stage.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Wesley Geer

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: You’ve probably encountered the cool groove of Winston Blissett on your radio at some point in time. He has a formidable resume of who’s who in pop music.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Winston Blissett

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: As former Buckcherry and Wallflowers member, California born and raised artist, Yogi, has a curriculum vitae which reads like an encyclopedia of musical legends.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Yogi Lonich

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Bassist and singer-songwriter Yolanda Charles has worked with Urban Species, Raw Stylus, DC Lee, Paul Weller, Eric Clapton, BB King, Roger Daltry, Van Morrison and even Michael Jackson.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Yolanda Charles

a:CmsArtistFull.a:Description: Yuji Adachi, best known as the guitarist ‘YOU’ from the Japanese rock band Dead End, started playing guitar when he was in his teens. He quickly gained a reputation among various guitarists and joined Dead End, one of the hiking heavy melodic rock bands, in 1986.
a:CmsArtistFull.a:Name: Yuji 'YOU' Adachi
